&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own capacity planning and staffing:&lt;/strong&gt; allocate engineers across parallel strategic projects, manage load and utilization, and anticipate delivery bottlenecks early.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive project delivery management:&lt;/strong&gt; own engineering delivery across deployments — milestones, dependencies, risk management, escalation paths, and stakeholder alignment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Establish time tracking and delivery visibility:&lt;/strong&gt; implement lightweight tracking and reporting that creates trusted insight into effort, progress, and capacity (without bureaucracy).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Provide technical leadership and escalation support:&lt;/strong&gt; guide architecture and implementation choices, review designs/code when needed, and unblock high-severity issues in production environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Create scalable field engineering practices:&lt;/strong&gt; build reusable patterns, playbooks, and standards that improve reliability, maintainability, and speed across deployments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shape the product via field learnings: &lt;/strong&gt;translate recurring customer needs into clear productization proposals and partner with Product/Core Engineering to reduce one-offs over time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner with customer engineering and enterprise stakeholders:&lt;/strong&gt; collaborate directly with customer teams (architecture, security, platform) to deliver outcomes and build long-term technical trust.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
